<p id="fs-idm225241056">The inverse proportional relation between <em data-effect="italics">K</em><sub>a</sub> and <em data-effect="italics">K</em><sub>b</sub> means <em data-effect="italics">the stronger the acid or base, the weaker its conjugate partner</em>. <a class="autogenerated-content" href="#CNX_Chem_14_03_strengths">Figure 14.7</a> illustrates this relation for several conjugate acid-base pairs.</p>
<div class="os-figure" id="CNX_Chem_14_03_strengths"><figure data-id="CNX_Chem_14_03_strengths">
